[h1]The length Property[/h1]

JavaScript arrays have useful[b] built-in[/b] properties and methods.

An array's [b]length [/b]property returns the number of it's elements.[code format="js" codeId="698"]var courses = ["HTML", "CSS", "JS"];
document.write([b]courses.length[/b]);
//Outputs 3[/code]
[note]The [b]length [/b]property is always one more than the highest array index.
If the array is empty, the length property returns [b]0[/b].[/note]
